<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="728" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d728">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.42157SA29/1302½</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde Park</hi>, N. Y.</placeName>,
                                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-05">September 5,
                                        1934</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Cordell</hi>: Will you see Frank Walsh on
                                St. Lawrence Treaty? I think he should <hi rend="italic">participate</hi> in any further plans for negotiations with
                                Canada.</p>
                            <p>He is as you know Chairman of the N. Y. State Authority—&amp; the
                                State owns the bed of the River!</p>
                            <p>I want to put the Treaty through.</p>
                            <p>As ever</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>